# Essor Framework

Source of truth: `agents/AGENTS.md`. The rules below are a compact summary.

Essor is signal-based with no virtual DOM. **`$`-prefixed variables auto-transform into reactive signals** via Babel.

## $ Prefix

```tsx
let $count = 0;              // signal(0)
const $items: Item[] = [];   // reactive([])
const $double = () => $x * 2; // computed

<div>{$count}</div>                // auto-unwrap
<button onClick={() => $count++}>  // .value++
<input bind:value={$name} />       // two-way binding
```

Mutate arrays in place: `$items.push(x)` ✅ — never `$items = [...$items, x]` ❌

## Rendering

- **Client-only:** `createApp(App, '#app')`
- **SSR/SSG:** `hydrate(App, '#app')` — NEVER `createApp`
- **Server:** `renderToString(App, {})` / `renderToStringAsync(App, {})`

## Key Patterns

```tsx
// Fragment:
function Row() { return <><td>A</td><td>B</td></>; }

// For:
<For each={$items} key={(item) => item.id} fallback={() => <p>Empty</p>}>
  {(item) => <li>{item.name}</li>}
</For>

// Suspense + resource:
const [data, { mutate, refetch }] = createResource(() => fetch('/api').then(r => r.json()));
<Suspense fallback={<Loading />}><div>{data()?.name}</div></Suspense>

// Forms:
<input bind:value={$email} />
<input bind:value={[$name, { trim: true }]} />
<input type="number" bind:value={$age} />     // auto number coercion
<input type="checkbox" bind:checked={$agree} />

// watch / untrack / nextTick:
watch(() => $x, (next, prev) => {});
untrack(() => $x);
await nextTick();
```

## Checklist
1. `$` on all reactive variables
2. Arrays mutated in place
3. `hydrate()` for SSR, `createApp()` for client-only
4. No browser globals in shared components
5. Timers/listeners cleaned up with `onDestroy()`
6. `For` has `key` when items reorder
7. Async data in `<Suspense>`
8. Imports only from `essor` or `@estjs/server`
